          "Csr": {
            "allOf": [
              { "$ref": "#/components/schemas/CsrBlob" },
              {
                "description": "<p>The certificate signing request (CSR) for the certificate you want to issue. You can use the following OpenSSL command to create the CSR and a 2048 bit RSA private key. </p> <p> <code>openssl req -new -newkey rsa:2048 -days 365 -keyout private/test_cert_priv_key.pem -out csr/test_cert_.csr</code> </p> <p>If you have a configuration file, you can use the following OpenSSL command. The <code>usr_cert</code> block in the configuration file contains your X509 version 3 extensions. </p> <p> <code>openssl req -new -config openssl_rsa.cnf -extensions usr_cert -newkey rsa:2048 -days -365 -keyout private/test_cert_priv_key.pem -out csr/test_cert_.csr</code> </p> <p>Note: A CSR must provide either a <i>subject name</i> or a <i>subject alternative name</i> or the request will be rejected. </p>"
              }
            ]
